<font face="Arial">
<center><h1> Situation Metaphor (Contd) </h1>

<h2><u> Interaction Model</u> </h2></center>
<h2>
  In Intearction model we formally define a particular situation as
   
<center> S&#161=S(L&#161,T&#161,A&#161,F&#161)  </center>


where

<ul>
<li>L&#161 gives physical location co-ordinates(latitude,Longitude)</li>

<li>T&#161 is a continuous period of time with start and end periods</li>

<li> A&#161 is a set of activity points with respect to all activites
engaged in work space </li>

<li> F&#161 describes the set of contextual factors affecting the
interaction </li>

<center> F&#161={<i> f1,f2,f3,.....fm</i> } </center>

<li> The relation ship between the situation and entities in given by</li>

<center> ID(S&#161)={<i> e1,e2,e3,.....en </i>}</center>

 which means that a particular situation is defined by the set of all
 entites that constitute that situation. 

</ul>
</h2>






